<div class="attendee-info-page">
  <section class="info-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="page-title">Attendee Information</h1>

      <!-- Cost Section -->
      <div class="info-card">
        <h2 class="section-heading">COST</h2>
        <p>The registration costs are:</p>
        <ul class="cost-list">
          <li><strong>1 child:</strong> $275 ($225 early registration)</li>
          <li><strong>2 children:</strong> $550 ($450 early registration)</li>
          <li><strong>3 or more children (family max):</strong> $650 ($500 early registration)</li>
          <li><strong>Early registration discounts ends March 31st 2026</strong></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="note">This fee does not cover the cost and therefore Kid's Camp is being subsidized. The actual cost is approximately $500 per student and donations are appreciated.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Parents Note Section -->
      <div class="info-card highlight">
        <h2 class="section-heading">PARENTS NOTE</h2>
        <p>Students should not arrive until Sunday at 4:00 PM. Counselors themselves are arriving earlier but require time to set up the campsites. Meal arrangements do not begin until Sunday evening.</p>
        <p><strong>Please label your child's belongings or they may not return with them!</strong> There is a <%= link_to "checklist for personal items", '/files/CamperChecklist.pdf', target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' %> attached. We ask you to please go over this list and ensure that your child comes to camp with all the items. Then sign the page so we know you have seen it. Thank you.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Medical Emergencies Section -->
      <div class="info-card">
        <h2 class="section-heading">MEDICAL EMERGENCIES</h2>
        <p>Medical forms are located at the main hall. Should an emergency arise, contact Bro. Jimmy Glover. Also, students should bring their own Health Insurance cards in the event of an emergency.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Camp Committee Section -->
      <div class="info-card">
        <h2 class="section-heading">CAMP COMMITTEE</h2>
        <p>Bro. Jimmy & Sis. Katie Glover, Sis. Laura Rodriguez, Bro. Greg & Sis. Michelle Robinson, Bro. Jason & Sis. Jenny Robinson, Bro. Seth & Sis. Felicity Robinson, Bro. Caleb & Sis. Bethany Osborn, Bro. Aaron & Sis. Molly McDonald.</p>
        <p class="important-note"><strong>EARLY ARRIVALS AND LATE DEPARTURES MUST MAKE THEIR INTENTIONS KNOWN TO A COMMITTEE MEMBER BEFORE ARRIVAL.</strong></p>
      </div>

      <!-- Other Things Section -->
      <div class="info-card">
        <h2 class="section-heading">OTHER THINGS YOU SHOULD KNOW</h2>

        <div class="subsection">
          <h3 class="subsection-heading">COOKING</h3>
          <p>All cooking will be done under the supervision of the counselors at each campsite. Food will be picked up at the main hall daily. A schedule for meals is provided.</p>
          <p class="note">*Please note the changes made to this year's Kids Camp menu. In order to have more nutritious options, dessert will only be provided with Sunday and Friday evening meals. If you would like desserts or other sweet treats during the week, please have your child bring a package, such as cookies, to share with their campmates.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
          <h3 class="subsection-heading">RESPONSIBILITY</h3>
          <p>a) Every student MUST have a medical consent form filled out and returned before the Camp.</p>
          <p>b) Each student is assigned to a counselor. The counselor will act as a parent and should be regarded with the same respect shown to your parent.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
          <h3 class="subsection-heading">TENTING</h3>
          <p>All students will camp with their respective counselors. They will share the duties relating to washrooms, food preparation, dishes, etc. Duty rosters will be prepared.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
          <h3 class="subsection-heading">DRESS</h3>
          <p>Students should dress appropriately for all Kid's Camp functions. Girls are required to wear dresses or skirts for classes. Boys are to wear long pants and collared shirts to classes, and no ripped jeans. If you have any questions in this regard, ask a counselor. See the <a href="<%= rules_path %>">camp rules</a> for more details.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
          <h3 class="subsection-heading">BOUNDARIES</h3>
          <p>Students must stay within the Camp grounds.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="subsection">
          <h3 class="subsection-heading">COUNSELING</h3>
          <p>For more information on what the counselling experience is like, please refer to our <a href="<%= counsellor_info_path %>">counselor FAQs</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

            <!-- Registration Section -->
      <div class="info-card">
        <h2 class="section-heading">REGISTRATION</h2>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <p><strong>For more information on registration, please contact Bro. James and Sis. Kristen Styles</strong></p>
          <p>
            <a href="tel:805-433-3409">805-433-3409</a><br>
            <a href="mailto:kidscampcalifornia@gmail.com">kidscampcalifornia@gmail.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</div>

